A path operation is FastAPI’s term for
an endpoint defined for a specific HTTP method and URL path. For example, a GET
request to /users can be handled by one path operation, while a POST request to
the same path can handle user creation.

Path operations are usually created
using decorators like {@app.get()
  } or {@app.post()
  }. They define how the API
responds to incoming requests. In interviews, explain that path operations are
the basic building blocks of a FastAPI application.
